                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 103.97/163: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                            Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-12">January 12,
                            1919</date>.<lb/>[Received January 13—12:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68. For Hoover.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Only yesterday I have been informed of the European Relief Administration. I
                        have delegated by wire Attolico to represent Italian Government at the first
                        meeting. I shall ask President Orlando on his return to appoint the two
                        permanent Italian delegates. I expect the new body will deal with matters
                        included in your telegram of the 7th in regard Roumania. Crespi.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
